issue.body:
Hi again Chris,

Sorry to pop this one out, You gotta blame uncle Billie from M$ for making such a pathetic browser. I found some strange errors in IE something like "Object expected" with SuperSelectors and this happens only in IE.

I debugged the source of SS and found it was not able to parse some Style sheet rules like body > p. There were two places where I had to wrap / patch the code with try and catch as below:

ONE AT FUNCTION _match_item

```
function _match_item(reg,className){
  try{
    var itemMatch=CSS.replace(/[\n\r]/gi,"").match(reg);
    if(itemMatch){
      itemMatch=itemMatch.join(", ");
    }
    if(itemMatch){
      $(itemMatch).addClass(className);
    }
  }catch(err){}
}
```

SECOND ONE AT FUNCTION _match_hover

```
function _match_hover(reg,className){
  try{
    var itemMatch=CSS.replace(/[\n\r]/gi,"").match(reg);
    if(itemMatch){
      itemMatch=itemMatch.join(", ");
    }
    if(itemMatch){
      $(itemMatch).hover(function(){
        $(this).addClass(className);
      },function(){
        $(this).removeClass(className);
      });
    }
  }catch(err){}
```

You can tell the difference man its your code. But for me wrapping it up inside try{} catch{} stopped that error from showing up.

