This is a huge patch that probably adds long awaited ability to have
configurable resources and objects.
As base I took my own XML parser from XLang project which is a bit strict but easy to use.
Currently there is one notable restriction: string parameters should not start immediately
after '>' character of an enclosing tag. This will give parse error.
DTD is not yet ready but it's comming soon.
Basicly it is like this in BNF:
config ::= '<config>' (cfgline)* '</config>';
cfgline ::= object-line | resource-line ;
object-line ::= '<object name="' className '"' ('/>' | paramlist '</object>') ;
resource-line ::= '<resource name="' className '"' (' mult="' integer '"')? ('/>' | paramlist '</resource>');
paramlist ::= (paramline)* ;
paramline ::= '<param name="' string '" value="' string '"/>' ;
className, string and integer non-terminals are self-explainory.
More information on parser available from the home page.
